戊.definition: fifth of the ten Heavenly Stems 十天干[shi2 tian1 gan1]; fifth in order; letter "E" or Roman "V" in list "A, B, C", or "I, II, III" etc; penta

戊五醇.definition: xylitol; also written 木糖醇[mu4 tang2 chun2]

戊午.definition: fifty-fifth year E7 of the 60 year cycle, e.g. 1978 or 2038

戊子.definition: twenty-fifth year E1 of the 60 year cycle, e.g. 2008 or 2068

戊寅.definition: fifteenth year E3 of the 60 year cycle, e.g. 1998 or 2058

戊戌.definition: thirty-fifth year E11 of the 60 year cycle, e.g. 1958 or 2018

戊戌六君子.definition: the Six Gentlemen Martyrs of the failed reform movement of 1898, executed in its aftermath, namely: Tan Sitong 譚嗣同|谭嗣同[Tan2 Si4 tong2], Lin Xu 林旭[Lin2 Xu4], Yang Shenxiu 楊深秀|杨深秀[Yang2 Shen1 xiu4], Liu Guangdi 劉光第|刘光第[Liu2 Guang1 di4], Kang Guangren 康廣仁|康广仁[Kang1 Guang3 ren2] and Yang Rui 楊銳|杨锐[Yang2 Rui4]

戊戌政變.definition: coup by Dowager Empress Cixi 慈禧太后[Ci2 xi3 tai4 hou4] ending the 1898 attempt to reform the Qing dynasty

戊戌維新.definition: Hundred Days Reform (1898), failed attempt to reform the Qing dynasty

戊戌變法.definition: Hundred Days Reform (1898), failed attempt to reform the Qing dynasty

戊申.definition: forty-fifth year E9 of the 60 year cycle, e.g. 1968 or 2028

戊糖.definition: pentose (CH2O)5, monosaccharide with five carbon atoms, such as ribose 核糖[he2 tang2]

戊辰.definition: fifth year E5 of the 60 year cycle, e.g. 1988 or 2048
